FBIS4-7273 "dreas083aa_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-083 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Five Power Defense Arrangement Exercises Begin Five Power Defense Arrangement Exercises Begin BK2604100794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 GMT 26 Apr 94 BK2604100794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia English BFN [Text] Fighter planes and warships from five nations started mock air and sea battles off Malaysia and Singapore today to test the region's only multilateral defense pact involving outside powers. The four-day joint air and sea exercises under the Five Power Defense Arrangement -- FPDA -- end on Friday. FPDA link Britain, Australia, New Zealand, Malaysia, and Singapore. All are members of the Commonwealth. Code-named ADEX 94-2, the exercise is taking place over Singapore and Malaysia and the South China Sea, an area of overlapping territorial claims. The exercise was coordinated from the Royal Malaysian Air Force base at Butterworth, headquarters of the Integrated Air Defense System.
